  "text": "Fermentation by intestinal microflora and selective stimulation of the growth and/or activity of intestinal bacteria associated with health and well-being. In vitro data supporting the selective stimulation of bacterial growth by inulin have been generated in numerous studies carried out either in defined pure culture fermentation or by using human feces in both batch and continuous culture [CITATION_1] .",
